4 suspend the rules to allow the Senator to change the Senator's vote.
5 (5) An error caused by a malfunction of the voting system may be corrected without a vote within 10
6 minutes of the malfunction.
7 S50-210. Absentee votes – restrictions. (1) An excused senator may file an absentee vote
8 authorization form to vote during the excused absence on any vote for which absentee voting is allowed.
9 (2) An excused senator shall sign an absentee vote authorization form that specifies the motion and the
10 desired vote.
11 (3) The absentee vote authorization form must be handed in at the rostrum by the party whip or
12 designated senator before voting on the motion has commenced.
13 (4) The absentee vote authorization may be revoked before the vote by the member who signed the
14 authorization.
15 (5) Absentee voting is not allowed on third reading.
16 (6) An excused senator may vote using the absentee form or through remote voting at any time without
17 consent of any legislative leader.
18 S50-220. Call of the Senate without a quorum. (1) In the absence of a quorum, a majority of
19 Senators physically and remotely present may compel the attendance of absent Senators by ordering a call of
20 the Senate. A call of the Senate is not in order if a majority of Senators are physically and remotely present.
21 (2) On a call of the Senate, a Senator who refuses to attend may be arrested by the Sergeant-at-Arms
22 or any other person, as the majority of the Senators present direct. When the attendance of an absent Senator
23 is secured and the Senate refuses to excuse the Senator's absence, the Senator may not be paid any expense
24 payments while absent and is liable for the expenses incurred in procuring the Senator's attendance.
25 (3) During a call of the Senate, all business must be suspended. After a call has been ordered, no
26 motion is in order except a motion to adjourn or remove the call. When a quorum has been achieved under the
27 call, the call is automatically lifted. The call may be removed by a two-thirds vote of the members physically or
28 remotely present.
