25 S60-10. Senate rules -- amendment -- adoption -- suspension. (1) A motion to amend or adopt a
26 rule of the Senate must be referred to the Rules Committee without debate. A rule of the Senate may be
27 amended or adopted only with the concurrence of a majority of the Senate and after 1 day's notice.
28 (2) Subject to subsection (3), a rule may be suspended temporarily by a three-fifths vote.
