8 S70-10. Nominations -- second term reappointments. (1) The Governor shall nominate and, by and
9 with the consent of the Senate, appoint all officers whose offices are established by the Montana Constitution or
10 which may be created by law and for whom appointment or election is not otherwise provided.
11 (2) If during a recess of the Senate a vacancy occurs in any office subject to Senate confirmation, the
12 Governor shall appoint some fit person to discharge the duties of the office until the next meeting of the Senate,
13 when the Governor shall nominate a person to fill the office.
14 (3) If the Governor is reelected to a second 4-year term of office, the Governor shall renominate all
15 retained officers that were previously confirmed pursuant to subsection (1). The Senate confirmation procedure
16 for a retained officer is the same as the confirmation procedure for a new appointment.
17 (4) A retained officer is an individual whose term would have expired at the end of the Governor’s first
18 4-year term if the Governor had not been reelected to a second consecutive term.
19 S70-20. Receiving nominations -- requesting bill drafts. (1) Nominations and renominations
20 received from the Governor must be:
21 (a) received by the President;
22 (b) delivered to the Secretary of the Senate; and
23 (c) read under Order of Business No. 4, messages from the Governor.
24 (2) The Secretary shall distribute a copy of the list of nominations and renominations to each Senator.
25 (3) (a) The President of the Senate shall submit a bill draft request for a resolution for each nominee or
26 each group of nominees within 2 days of receiving a communication from the governor read under Order of
27 Business No. 4. These bill draft requests will not count against any bill draft request limit imposed on the
28 President of the Senate.
